    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup centered around **Kyle Tucker** (77.26) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66). **Kyle Tucker** represents our most compelling start, buoyed by a favorable matchup against Landen Roupp and wind conditions that boost his output potential. Similarly, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Brady House** (63.19) benefit significantly from a prime matchup against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez, whose 6.36 xERA suggests a high-scoring environment for the top of our order. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.68) remains an elite cornerstone, his value today is primarily driven by his impressive 0.384 xwOBA and a soft matchup against Jack Kochanowicz, making him a reliable pivot if the higher-variance plays face turbulence.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the rain risk (35%) hovering over the matchups involving **Andy Pages** (61.82) and **Kyle Tucker**. While both are strong starts based on their projected offensive output, any weather-related delays could impact their efficiency. The most difficult decision at the margins was excluding **Miguel Vargas** (53.97) from the active roster. While **Miguel Vargas** offers solid plate discipline and a favorable matchup profile, the optimizer favored **Nolan Schanuel** (56.47) and **Liam Hicks** (52.73) due to their specific platoon advantages and higher reliability in the current batting order projections. \n\nFinally, managers should monitor the status of **Gunnar Henderson** (56.78). Although his score remains strong, he is facing a challenging assignment against Kris Bubic; the decision to keep him active is largely dictated by his role as a primary source of SB, a scarcity we are prioritizing in today\u2019s construction. Despite the benching of veterans like **Marcell Ozuna** (52.65), the focus today remains on exploiting the pitching weaknesses of the opposition to maximize our 5x5 categorical output.",
